Cell.Text: [S] So, he says to petition Malacath for relief? Interesting.

Node.Caption: DA06Stage30AtubForcegreetTopic: Yamarz told me to go to Malacath.

Cell.Text: G|Perhaps. But he spoke of this "curse" to you, which means it has deeply affected him. | It may be worth attempting contact with Malacath after all. | Go to Malacath's shrine, southeast of Largashbur. See if perhaps he will aid us after all.

Node.Caption: DA06Stage30AtubResponse1: He was just trying to get rid of me.

Cell.Text: G|Yes, but he offered it as an idea. Perhaps he hopes it will be helpful, but does not wish to risk personal failure. | You should do as he says. Go to Malacath's shrine, northwest of here, and ask for his help. See what happens.

Node.Caption: DA06Stage30AtubResponse2: He didn't seem to think it would do any good.

Cell.Text: G|His shrine lies northwest of Largashbur. I am unsure that he will listen, but it cannot hurt.
Who are you? Why do you dare petition the great Malacath?

[S] Yamarz sends you to me? | The big, strong leader won't come himself? No respect! | Grrr... If Yamarz wishes his tribe to be free, he needs to listen with the ears of the wind. You tell his wise woman that, little one. | She'll know what to do.

Node.Caption: DA06Stage30ShrineResponse1: You're going to break if I pick this line.

Cell.Text: Yamarz sent you to me? The great, powerful leader didn't come himself? No respect at all!

Node.Caption: DA06Stage30ShrineTestResponse1: Yamarz wishes to be free of his curse.

Cell.Text: The Orcs may be Malacath's chosen, but Malacath won't help those who don't help themselves!

Node.Caption: DA06Stage30ShrineFollowUp1: He didn't seem to think you would help at all.

Cell.Text: [S] If Yamarz wants freedom from his curse, he needs to listen with the ears of the wind. You tell his wise-woman that, little one!

Node.Caption: Da06Stage30ShrineFinal: So what should I tell him?

Cell.Text: Yamarz is a fool for sending someone else to do his work!

Node.Caption: DA06Stage30ShrineFollowUp2: He asked that I come in his place.

Cell.Text: Almost ever since he became leader of the tribe. | He killed Shagrol in combat, which none of us thought possible. But the winner is made Chief. That is how it is done.

Node.Caption: DA06Stage30AtubCurseTopic: How long has Yamarz been cursed?
